responses.question: Are you talkative?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「If I find common ground, I can be quite chatty. There's even been a time or two where I've fallen asleep in the middle of a conversation. But, if we don't have anything to talk about then it's awkward. And I'm not fond of awkward situations!」

responses.question: Are you reserved?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Hmm... I'm usually pretty reserved in public. I don't have much of a reason to speak up or involve myself in what others are doing. But, around friends or small groups, I'm actually fairly talkative. I'm a bit of a chatterbox, I guess you could say.」

responses.question: Are you full of energy?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Quite a bit, actually. I don't have a problem with waking up early or staying up late. And I actually don't mind not having a lot of downtime between work. I would even go as far to say that I could be described as hyperactive.」

responses.question: Do you generate a lot of enthusiasm?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Oh yes, most definitely. If it's something I'm passionate about, I'll get very excited and animated about it. I can go on and on about what it is that I love and why it's so interesting, or fun, or special. I also have been told that my passion and enthusiasm is contagious. So others can get just as excited about it as I do.」

responses.question: Do you tend to be quiet?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「It really depends on the situation. Around groups and especially when I don't know a lot of the people, I can be quite reserved and hesitant to speak. In small groups with people I'm more familiar with, I can talk quite a bit and get quite animated. And then when I'm by myself or with one friend alone, it's an actual effort to be quiet. Sometimes I'll even talk to myself to fill in the air of silence just for the sound of it.」

responses.question: Do you have an assertive personality?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, I would say so. If I need to step up, I will without hesitation. And, if I need to make my stance or opinions know, I will speak up and make myself very clear on what it is I need to say. Though, that's not to say I'm confrontational. I won't go out of my way to confront people or fight with them, but if I think something needs to be said, nobody is going to stop me from saying it, either.」

responses.question: Are you sometimes shy, inhibited?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I do have a tendency to get shy or timid around large groups or unfamiliar people. I don't like being the center of attention and tend to keep to myself when given the chance. As with most things, that can be changed with time and familiarity. If I've grown to know and feel comfortable around you or anyone else, then my shyness tends to disappear and I start to be my normal, carefree and animated self around them.」

responses.question: Are you outgoing, sociable?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I do consider myself to be outgoing and sociable. Though, I am picky about who I'm outgoing and sociable with. When I'm with friends or people I'm familiar with, I'm almost always in full-volume, talkative mode. But, when I'm around unfamiliar people or in groups, I tend to keep to myself until I get to know someone better. I would say I've been described as "outgoing and sociable" and "quiet and introverted" by different people based on the situation.」

responses.question: Are you depressed, blue?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Depressed? No, I don't think so. I'm not a particularly moody person. I do often get bored if I don't have anything to keep my mind or body occupied. However, I can be quite content just thinking about things to myself.」

responses.question: Are you relaxed and handle stress well?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I don't get stressed out often. I am a very calm, easy-going person, and it takes a lot of work to get me riled up. However, when I do get stressed out, it's not something to be taken lightly. I'm not the yelling, throwing things kind of person when I'm angry, if that makes sense. But I can definitely shut down and become closed-off if someone or something pushes my buttons too much.」

responses.question: Can you be tense?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「In some situations, yes. As I said before, it takes a lot to stress me out. But, when it comes down to life or death or something like that, I'm definitely able to feel a bit more... "tense". Also, if I'm arguing or in a debate, I can get a bit heated. But it has to be something I actually care about or I won't get too defensive.」

responses.question: Do you worry a lot?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I do tend to overthink and worry about things quite a bit. Sometimes it's rational and other times it's irrational. Some of it is about the consequences and outcomes of my own actions, but other times it could be about something small that I'm worried about someone else. Other times it's just worry over what the future may hold.」

responses.question: Are you emotionally stable, not easily upset?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I am very emotionally stable, yes. It takes a lot to get me truly upset about something. I can still get a little frustrated or annoyed in a debate or a conflict, but if someone just happens to accidentally hurt my feelings, I tend to brush it aside and move on quickly. After all, it would be unreasonable to stay upset over a silly, offhand remark after a little while.」

responses.question: Can you be moody?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, I can get moody sometimes. Especially when I'm bored, or when I'm hungry or tired. I've also been known to get moody during arguments when someone doesn't seem to be fully understanding or accepting my logic. When it comes down to it, my mood depends on quite a few variables at any given time.」

responses.question: Do you remain calm in tense situations?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, I would say so. As I mentioned before, it takes a lot to stress me out. Even when I'm angry, it's almost never shown outwardly. Unless you know me well, you wouldn't even know by looking at me if I was angry or nervous about something. Even in dangerous situations, I tend to be as calm and quiet as ever.」

responses.question: Do you get nervous easily?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「No, I would say I have a pretty strong control of my nerves. It would take quite a bit to make me genuinely nervous. I would say the main time where I get nervous most often is when I'm anticipating something important to me, but even then, it's a rarity that I get overly nervous, to the point of sweating or trembling. I guess most of the time, I just never feel like I have a reason to be nervous.」

responses.question: Do you do a thorough job?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I always try my best at everything I do. Whether it's homework, chores, or an activity. I wouldn't want to half-do anything, especially not anything I consider important.」

responses.question: Can you be somewhat careless?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Oh, definitely. I'm pretty clumsy, both in my mind and body. It feels like I trip over my own feet or bump into stationary objects more often than a lot of other people. Not to mention the number of times I've forgotten or lost things because I left them somewhere silly. So yes, careless is definitely a good word to describe me.」

responses.question: Are you a reliable worker?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I like to think so. Any project or task I take up, it gets done. No matter how long it takes, how repetitive or monotonous the task becomes, if I set my mind to it, I don't stop until it's finished. Whether it's homework, an art project, or anything else.」

responses.question: Do you tend to be disorganized?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I would love to deny it, but I cannot. I'm usually quite sloppy. My room and other personal spaces are quite messy, and I don't put a lot of attention to keeping them neat. I'm aware it's not a good habit, but unfortunately, I tend to put off organizing everything or cleaning up if it's not something I'm being forced to do.」

responses.question: Do you tend to be lazy?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I would say yes, quite frequently. If it's something I have to do or I don't feel like doing something, I tend to put it off as much as possible. Even for small things, I will often put off for days at a time just because I'm not in the mood or just don't care very much. I don't like to admit it, but unfortunately, I am rather lazy at times.」

responses.question: Do you persevere until the task is finished?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Absolutely. It doesn't matter how long it takes, or how difficult it would be, I will finish what I've started. There have even been times where I will take it upon myself to complete a task that wasn't even assigned to me because I wanted to be helpful. I would never leave something unfinished, especially if it would impact someone else or myself.」

responses.question: Do you do things efficiently?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I prefer to do things as cleanly and efficiently as possible. Even if it means taking a little longer. I tend to have a bit of a perfectionist streak in me, and I don't like having any unnecessary wasted time. So, whenever I have to do something that requires me doing it alone, I make sure that I do absolutely everything in the most perfect way that I'm able to. This includes things as small as a little project I've been given or as significant as a group assignment or team project that's being graded.」

responses.question: Do you make plans and follow through with them?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I will make plans, yes. Though, making plans and actually following through with them in the intended timeline is something I have difficulty with. While I will always get it done, it will almost never be done at the time I originally planned. I do tend to procrastinate a lot and leave things off until the last minute. As long as it gets done, though, I never consider myself to have failed. After all, I've learned that deadlines are made to be pushed back.」

responses.question: Are you easily distracted?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Extremely so. There are quite a few things that will easily distract me from whatever I'm currently working on because they're either more interesting or appealing to my current interests. Whether it be something I see in the room, a comment or question someone makes towards me, or even just my thoughts themselves. I find it very easy to fall into the habit of getting distracted and forgetting about the task I was actually supposed to be doing.」

responses.question: Do you tend to find fault with others?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「That's an interesting question. I don't think I would. Everyone has their own quirks and shortcomings. It wouldn't do any good to judge people over silly things like that. And, everyone is allowed an opinion.」

responses.question: Are you helpful and unselfish with others?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I try to be, yes. I don't like to see people upset or hurt in any way. I've been told that I can be insensitive or oblivious to feelings sometimes but that's not intentional. I always tell people if they want or need something, don't hesitate to ask me directly.」

responses.question: Do you start quarrels with others?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I never instigate or start arguments. That would go against my personal motto, "Live and let live". If a confrontation arises I'll defend my side of things and try to end the argument. I try to avoid confrontation entirely whenever possible, so if someone else has a problem with me, I try not to respond with hostility.」

responses.question: Do you have a forgiving nature?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I feel that's something to be proud of, yes. So long as someone is truly sorry for what they've done, I can forgive them. After all, holding grudges is unhealthy and pointless. Even if I don't say it out loud, I try to forgive people for their mistakes. However, that doesn't mean I'll ever forget.」

responses.question: Are you generally trusting?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「In general, yes. I usually tend to trust people, sometimes maybe a little too quickly. But, that doesn't mean that there isn't some skepticism in me. I'm not foolish enough to 100% believe anything and everything that's said to me. I'll always think about the possibility that someone might be lying or hiding something.」

responses.question: Can you be cold and aloof?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, I can. I tend to have walls of secrecy and distance between myself and others quite a bit in general. A lot of my friends have told me that I'm hard to get to know on a deeper level. I'm friendly and personable most of the time, but I don't always share every detail about myself. I like to keep a certain level of mystery, and I'm rarely, if ever, completely open and vulnerable with my emotions and thoughts.」

responses.question: Are you considerate and kind to almost everyone?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, very much so. I try to treat people well and be as considerate as possible, even to those who are unkind or indifferent to me. It's important to be kind to everyone you meet, at least until they give you a reason to no longer continue being kind. I don't believe in hating people until they give me a good reason to hate them, but I won't hesitate to become their worst enemy when they do, either.」

responses.question: Are you sometimes rude to others?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I would consider my bluntness to be the same as rudeness to some people. My way of speaking to people is often straightforward or to-the-point. I don't mean to come off as rude to those people, but I believe that some people could misinterpret that. So yes, I would say I have been rude to others before, though never on purpose.」

responses.question: Do you like to cooperate with others?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I would consider myself a team player, yes. I don't mind cooperating with others to help a team towards a shared goal or achieve something collectively. I actually prefer working together with someone else over working by myself most of the time, as I think it gives a different perspective on something that can be incredibly useful. It gives me new ideas, new insight, and allows me to see things through a different lens that I might not have been able to come up with otherwise.」

responses.question: Do you come up with new ideas?
responses.response_open:
凉宫春日: 「You're asking some pretty random questions. Anyways, yes, I do. But, they're not usually anything that could be put to use in the real world.

And, even the ones I do have that would "work" are usually just fun or interesting hypotheticals. Like, what if gravity shifted slightly to the left all day? Or what if everyone suddenly turned into a giant jellyfish? That sort of thing. Just for fun, really.」

responses.question: Are you curious about many different things?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Oh yes, very. I've been known to study about a bunch of random, unrelated things for hours on end just because I wanted to know more about them. Anything that catches my attention, I'll at least try to learn something about it, even if it's minor. For example, not too long ago, I suddenly became interested in the construction of ancient temples. So much so that I looked up some articles on it and read up on the topic.」

responses.question: Are you ingenious, a deep thinker?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, I would like to believe so. When I start to overthink and dwell on things, I can come up with some... strange scenarios. I'm a daydreamer at heart, so I can easily get lost in my imagination and run with a thought if I focus on it long enough.」

responses.question: Do you have an active imagination?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Oh yes, I do. I would even consider it one of my strongest traits. I have a very active and imaginative mind, so it's very easy for me to dive into my imagination and get lost in whatever scenario it comes up with. I am known for having more than one wacky theories about everything. Some very reasonable, others completely absurd and outlandish.」

responses.question: Are you inventive?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, very much. I will never be one to claim that I'm a genius or brilliant with my ideas. But, I do try my best to be creative and come up with original concepts that I haven't seen anywhere else. Sometimes I'll even go a little crazy and start mixing and matching a bunch of wacky ideas together to see what happens. It's all in good fun, and some of my better creations have come from my crazier ideas.」

responses.question: Do you value artistic, aesthetic experiences?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I absolutely do. I value art, whether it be artistic drawings, music, or even just the scenery in a place. I enjoy studying the aesthetics and beauty of things in general. I don't mean it to sound so pretentious, but I truly find the small details and subtleties that people don't often think about to be just as, if not more interesting than the overall image.」

responses.question: Do you prefer work that is routine?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Yes, I do. I find routine to be comforting. The more repetitive and predictable something is, the better I feel doing it. I would rather do the same tasks everyday than have them constantly changing or have to remember some new instructions every time I do something. Routine feels organized and makes things feel less chaotic that way.」

responses.question: Do you like to reflect, play with ideas?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I love to reflect and speculate on ideas. I think deep, internal thought is a very important thing, and I tend to find pleasure in reflecting upon myself, my goals, or the universe in general. I often like to spend hours, even days, just contemplating different outcomes for every possible choice and imagining different scenarios in my head. I've often gotten lost in my own mind and forgotten about the real world due to the amount of time I reflect and think.」

responses.question: Do you have few artistic interests?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「Oh, no. I consider myself to have quite the artistic side to me. Whether it be drawing, music, writing, or whatever else, I have a great love and passion for all forms of art. Whenever I have the free time and motivation, I'll try to create something, and I even aspire to make an actual career of it.」

responses.question: Are you sophisticated in art, music, or literature?
responses.response_open: 凉宫春日: 「I would say I'm decently sophisticated in literature and music, and I can definitely say I'm quite educated in art. Of course, I'm not a expert by any means and there are always new things to learn and discover. But, that's one of the parts I find truly enjoyable. To always be learning, exploring, and discovering new ideas and insights no matter the topic. So, in many ways, I would consider myself to be fairly well educated in art, literature, and music.」
